> This chicken doesn’t just cross the road. It races down it at lightning speed. You
> can have these crispy, breadcrumb-coated cutlets on the table in 20 minutes flat
> (and that includes the toasty garlic bread and green salad that come on the side).
> The only thing we suggest slowing down for is savoring all those scrumptious flavors
> once they’re on your plate.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #oven or #toaster oven{} to 400 degrees. Mince or grate
@garlic{2%cloves}. Put garlic, @butter{2%tbsp}, and @Italian seasoning{1%tsp} in a small,
microwave-safe #bowl (we'll use the rest of the seasoning later). Heat in #microwave
until butter is melted, about ~{30%seconds}.

Halve @demi-baguettes{2} lengthwise and place on a #baking sheet{} cut-side up. Brush
with garlic butter. Toast in #oven or toaster oven until golden brown, about
~{8-10%minutes}.

Heat @vegetable oil{2%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{}
if you have one). Mix together @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and remaining @Italian
seasoning{1%tbsp} on a #plate. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place @chicken breasts{10%oz}
on another #plate and season with salt and pepper. Brush all over with @sour cream{1%tbsp}
(we sent more). Dip into panko mixture, pressing to adhere.

Add chicken to #pan and cook until no longer pink in center and panko is golden brown,
about ~{2-4%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside on a paper-towel-lined
#plate.

While chicken cooks, cut @Roma tomato{1} into wedges. Halve @lemon{1}; cut one half
into wedges. Toss tomato, @dried cranberries{1%oz}, and @arugula{2%oz} with a squeeze
of lemon and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a medium #bowl. Season with salt,
pepper, and more lemon (to taste).

Divide chicken, salad, and garlic toasts between plates. Serve with lemon wedges on
the side for squeezing over.